The paper deals with the problem of optimizing the dispatching of orders to vehicles and fleet management in online ride-hailing platforms using a multi-agent reinforcement learning framework. This involves coordination between agents, hierarchical reinforcement learning, dealing with heterogeneous and variant action spaces, and decision-making in a hierarchical way. These topics are all related to artificial intelligence and machine learning, specifically in the areas of reinforcement learning, multi-agent systems, and decision-making. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
